Four of the six suspects who were arrested in connection with the Naidoo family kidnapping and triple murder in Northcliff were remanded in custody, reports the Northcliff Melville Times.The four suspects briefly appeared in the Johannesburg Magistrates Court on 12 June.Gauteng police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubela said the suspects were expected back in the dock on 19 June for a formal bail application. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on northcliffmelvilletimes.co.za